2014-04-28  Michael Meissner  <meissner@linux.vnet.ibm.com>

	* config.host (powerpc*-*-linux*): Add support to build __float128
	on PowerPC systems.

	* soft-fp/quad.h (TFtype): On PowerPC systems with the __float128
	keyword, use __float128 instead of attribute((mode(TF))).

	* config/rs6000/float128-vsx.h: New file to allow building IEEE
	128-bit floating point support on PowerPC, supporting two
	different ABI's, one using the VSX extensions, and the other not
	using VSX.
	* config/rs6000/float128-novsx.h: Likewise.
	* config/rs6000/t-float128: Likewise.
